from math import floor

def calculate_sum_with_reversed_second_number(a1: int, a2: int) -> int:
    rev = 1
    while a2 > 0:
        a = int(a2 % 10)
        rev = rev * 10 + a
        a2 = floor(a2 / 10)
    return a1 + rev
